<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-82-0447 </DOCNO><TEXT>A new experiment will measure the muon g-2 value with 20 times betterprecision than it is presently known. To reach this goal, the magneticfield in the muon storage ring must be known to be a part in 10{sup 7}.This can be achieved by storing singly charged heavy ions in the ringand measuring their cyclotron frequency. 13 refs., 1 fig.</TEXT></DOC>